{comment: Verse 1}
[C]  [G]  [Em]  [Dsus4]

[C]You got a [G]fast car
[Em]I want a [Dsus4]ticket to anywhere
[C]Maybe we make a [G]deal
[Em]Maybe together [Dsus4]we can get somewhere
[C]Any place is [G]better
[Em]Startin' from zero, [Dsus4]got nothin' to lose
[C]Maybe we'll make [G]somethin'
[Em]Me, myself, I [Dsus4]got nothin' to prove

[C]  [G]  [Em]  [Dsus4]
[C]  [G]  [Em]  [Dsus4]

[C]You got a [G]fast car
[Em]I got a plan    [Dsus4]to get us outta here
And [C]work another [G]convenience store
[Em]Managed to save [Dsus4]just a little bit of money
[C]Won't have to drive [G]too far
Just [Em]across the border [Dsus4]and into the city
[C]You and I [G]can both get jobs
[Em]Finally see [Dsus4]what it means to be livin'

[C]  [G]  [Em]  [Dsus4]
[C]  [G]  [Em]  [Dsus4]

See, [C]my old man's [G]got a problem
[Em]He live in the bottle, [Dsus4]that's the way it is
He said: his [C]body's too old [G]for workin'
His [Em]body's too young    [Dsus4]to look like his
So [C]mama went off [G]and left him
She [Em]wanted more from life [Dsus4]than he could give
I said: [C]Somebody's gotta [G]take care of him
So [Em]I quit school and [Dsus4]that's what I did

[C]  [G]  [Em]  [Dsus4]
[C]  [G]  [Em]  [Dsus4]

[C]You got a [G]fast car
